Tankey Game  1.0
Tankey es un juego sobre un gorila. Este gorila trepa por un árbol infinito, pero a medida que sube se enfrenta a un problema: debe esquivar las ramas que se avecinan sobre él. Moviéndose de un lado al otro... ¿Podrá lograrlo?

710 static void* cgltf_calloc(cgltf_options* options, size_t element_size, cgltf_size count)
711 {
712  if (SIZE_MAX / element_size < count)
713  {
714  return NULL;
715  }
716  void* result = options->memory_alloc(options->memory_user_data, element_size * count);
717  if (!result)
718  {
719  return NULL;
720  }
721  memset(result, 0, element_size * count);
722  return result;
723 }

727 cgltf_result cgltf_parse(const cgltf_options* options, const void* data, cgltf_size size, cgltf_data** out_data)
728 {
729  if (size < GlbHeaderSize)
730  {
731  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
732  }
733 
734  if (options == NULL)
735  {
736  return cgltf_result_invalid_options;
737  }
738 
739  cgltf_options fixed_options = *options;
740  if (fixed_options.memory_alloc == NULL)
741  {
742  fixed_options.memory_alloc = &cgltf_default_alloc;
743  }
744  if (fixed_options.memory_free == NULL)
745  {
746  fixed_options.memory_free = &cgltf_default_free;
747  }
748 
749  uint32_t tmp;
750  // Magic
751  memcpy(&tmp, data, 4);
752  if (tmp != GlbMagic)
753  {
754  if (fixed_options.type == cgltf_file_type_invalid)
755  {
756  fixed_options.type = cgltf_file_type_gltf;
757  }
758  else if (fixed_options.type == cgltf_file_type_glb)
759  {
760  return cgltf_result_unknown_format;
761  }
762  }
763 
764  if (fixed_options.type == cgltf_file_type_gltf)
765  {
766  cgltf_result json_result = cgltf_parse_json(&fixed_options, (const uint8_t*)data, size, out_data);
767  if (json_result != cgltf_result_success)
768  {
769  return json_result;
770  }
771 
772  (*out_data)->file_type = cgltf_file_type_gltf;
773 
774  return cgltf_result_success;
775  }
776 
777  const uint8_t* ptr = (const uint8_t*)data;
778  // Version
779  memcpy(&tmp, ptr + 4, 4);
780  uint32_t version = tmp;
781  if (version != GlbVersion)
782  {
783  return version < GlbVersion ? cgltf_result_legacy_gltf : cgltf_result_unknown_format;
784  }
785 
786  // Total length
787  memcpy(&tmp, ptr + 8, 4);
788  if (tmp > size)
789  {
790  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
791  }
792 
793  const uint8_t* json_chunk = ptr + GlbHeaderSize;
794 
795  if (GlbHeaderSize + GlbChunkHeaderSize > size)
796  {
797  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
798  }
799 
800  // JSON chunk: length
801  uint32_t json_length;
802  memcpy(&json_length, json_chunk, 4);
803  if (GlbHeaderSize + GlbChunkHeaderSize + json_length > size)
804  {
805  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
806  }
807 
808  // JSON chunk: magic
809  memcpy(&tmp, json_chunk + 4, 4);
810  if (tmp != GlbMagicJsonChunk)
811  {
812  return cgltf_result_unknown_format;
813  }
814 
815  json_chunk += GlbChunkHeaderSize;
816 
817  const void* bin = 0;
818  cgltf_size bin_size = 0;
819 
820  if (GlbHeaderSize + GlbChunkHeaderSize + json_length + GlbChunkHeaderSize <= size)
821  {
822  // We can read another chunk
823  const uint8_t* bin_chunk = json_chunk + json_length;
824 
825  // Bin chunk: length
826  uint32_t bin_length;
827  memcpy(&bin_length, bin_chunk, 4);
828  if (GlbHeaderSize + GlbChunkHeaderSize + json_length + GlbChunkHeaderSize + bin_length > size)
829  {
830  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
831  }
832 
833  // Bin chunk: magic
834  memcpy(&tmp, bin_chunk + 4, 4);
835  if (tmp != GlbMagicBinChunk)
836  {
837  return cgltf_result_unknown_format;
838  }
839 
840  bin_chunk += GlbChunkHeaderSize;
841 
842  bin = bin_chunk;
843  bin_size = bin_length;
844  }
845 
846  cgltf_result json_result = cgltf_parse_json(&fixed_options, json_chunk, json_length, out_data);
847  if (json_result != cgltf_result_success)
848  {
849  return json_result;
850  }
851 
852  (*out_data)->file_type = cgltf_file_type_glb;
853  (*out_data)->bin = bin;
854  (*out_data)->bin_size = bin_size;
855 
856  return cgltf_result_success;
857 }
858 
859 cgltf_result cgltf_parse_file(const cgltf_options* options, const char* path, cgltf_data** out_data)
860 {
861  if (options == NULL)
862  {
863  return cgltf_result_invalid_options;
864  }
865 
866  void* (*memory_alloc)(void*, cgltf_size) = options->memory_alloc ? options->memory_alloc : &cgltf_default_alloc;
867  void (*memory_free)(void*, void*) = options->memory_free ? options->memory_free : &cgltf_default_free;
868 
869  FILE* file = fopen(path, "rb");
870  if (!file)
871  {
872  return cgltf_result_file_not_found;
873  }
874 
875  fseek(file, 0, SEEK_END);
876 
877  long length = ftell(file);
878  if (length < 0)
879  {
880  fclose(file);
881  return cgltf_result_io_error;
882  }
883 
884  fseek(file, 0, SEEK_SET);
885 
886  char* file_data = (char*)memory_alloc(options->memory_user_data, length);
887  if (!file_data)
888  {
889  fclose(file);
890  return cgltf_result_out_of_memory;
891  }
892 
893  cgltf_size file_size = (cgltf_size)length;
894  cgltf_size read_size = fread(file_data, 1, file_size, file);
895 
896  fclose(file);
897 
898  if (read_size != file_size)
899  {
900  memory_free(options->memory_user_data, file_data);
901  return cgltf_result_io_error;
902  }
903 
904  cgltf_result result = cgltf_parse(options, file_data, file_size, out_data);
905 
906  if (result != cgltf_result_success)
907  {
908  memory_free(options->memory_user_data, file_data);
909  return result;
910  }
911 
912  (*out_data)->file_data = file_data;
913 
914  return cgltf_result_success;
915 }

917 static void cgltf_combine_paths(char* path, const char* base, const char* uri)
918 {
919  const char* s0 = strrchr(base, '/');
920  const char* s1 = strrchr(base, '\\');
921  const char* slash = s0 ? (s1 && s1 > s0 ? s1 : s0) : s1;
922 
923  if (slash)
924  {
925  size_t prefix = slash - base + 1;
926 
927  strncpy(path, base, prefix);
928  strcpy(path + prefix, uri);
929  }
930  else
931  {
932  strcpy(path, uri);
933  }
934 }

936 static cgltf_result cgltf_load_buffer_file(const cgltf_options* options, cgltf_size size, const char* uri, const char* gltf_path, void** out_data)
937 {
938  void* (*memory_alloc)(void*, cgltf_size) = options->memory_alloc ? options->memory_alloc : &cgltf_default_alloc;
939  void (*memory_free)(void*, void*) = options->memory_free ? options->memory_free : &cgltf_default_free;
940 
941  char* path = (char*)memory_alloc(options->memory_user_data, strlen(uri) + strlen(gltf_path) + 1);
942  if (!path)
943  {
944  return cgltf_result_out_of_memory;
945  }
946 
947  cgltf_combine_paths(path, gltf_path, uri);
948 
949  FILE* file = fopen(path, "rb");
950 
951  memory_free(options->memory_user_data, path);
952 
953  if (!file)
954  {
955  return cgltf_result_file_not_found;
956  }
957 
958  char* file_data = (char*)memory_alloc(options->memory_user_data, size);
959  if (!file_data)
960  {
961  fclose(file);
962  return cgltf_result_out_of_memory;
963  }
964 
965  cgltf_size read_size = fread(file_data, 1, size, file);
966 
967  fclose(file);
968 
969  if (read_size != size)
970  {
971  memory_free(options->memory_user_data, file_data);
972  return cgltf_result_io_error;
973  }
974 
975  *out_data = file_data;
976 
977  return cgltf_result_success;
978 }
979 
980 cgltf_result cgltf_load_buffer_base64(const cgltf_options* options, cgltf_size size, const char* base64, void** out_data)
981 {
982  void* (*memory_alloc)(void*, cgltf_size) = options->memory_alloc ? options->memory_alloc : &cgltf_default_alloc;
983  void (*memory_free)(void*, void*) = options->memory_free ? options->memory_free : &cgltf_default_free;
984 
985  unsigned char* data = (unsigned char*)memory_alloc(options->memory_user_data, size);
986  if (!data)
987  {
988  return cgltf_result_out_of_memory;
989  }
990 
991  unsigned int buffer = 0;
992  unsigned int buffer_bits = 0;
993 
994  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < size; ++i)
995  {
996  while (buffer_bits < 8)
997  {
998  char ch = *base64++;
999 
1000  int index =
1001  (unsigned)(ch - 'A') < 26 ? (ch - 'A') :
1002  (unsigned)(ch - 'a') < 26 ? (ch - 'a') + 26 :
1003  (unsigned)(ch - '0') < 10 ? (ch - '0') + 52 :
1004  ch == '+' ? 62 :
1005  ch == '/' ? 63 :
1006  -1;
1007 
1008  if (index < 0)
1009  {
1010  memory_free(options->memory_user_data, data);
1011  return cgltf_result_io_error;
1012  }
1013 
1014  buffer = (buffer << 6) | index;
1015  buffer_bits += 6;
1016  }
1017 
1018  data[i] = (unsigned char)(buffer >> (buffer_bits - 8));
1019  buffer_bits -= 8;
1020  }
1021 
1022  *out_data = data;
1023 
1024  return cgltf_result_success;
1025 }

1027 cgltf_result cgltf_load_buffers(const cgltf_options* options, cgltf_data* data, const char* gltf_path)
1028 {
1029  if (options == NULL)
1030  {
1031  return cgltf_result_invalid_options;
1032  }
1033 
1034  if (data->buffers_count && data->buffers[0].data == NULL && data->buffers[0].uri == NULL && data->bin)
1035  {
1036  if (data->bin_size < data->buffers[0].size)
1037  {
1038  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
1039  }
1040 
1041  data->buffers[0].data = (void*)data->bin;
1042  }
1043 
1044  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->buffers_count; ++i)
1045  {
1046  if (data->buffers[i].data)
1047  {
1048  continue;
1049  }
1050 
1051  const char* uri = data->buffers[i].uri;
1052 
1053  if (uri == NULL)
1054  {
1055  continue;
1056  }
1057 
1058  if (strncmp(uri, "data:", 5) == 0)
1059  {
1060  const char* comma = strchr(uri, ',');
1061 
1062  if (comma && comma - uri >= 7 && strncmp(comma - 7, ";base64", 7) == 0)
1063  {
1064  cgltf_result res = cgltf_load_buffer_base64(options, data->buffers[i].size, comma + 1, &data->buffers[i].data);
1065 
1066  if (res != cgltf_result_success)
1067  {
1068  return res;
1069  }
1070  }
1071  else
1072  {
1073  return cgltf_result_unknown_format;
1074  }
1075  }
1076  else if (strstr(uri, "://") == NULL && gltf_path)
1077  {
1078  cgltf_result res = cgltf_load_buffer_file(options, data->buffers[i].size, uri, gltf_path, &data->buffers[i].data);
1079 
1080  if (res != cgltf_result_success)
1081  {
1082  return res;
1083  }
1084  }
1085  else
1086  {
1087  return cgltf_result_unknown_format;
1088  }
1089  }
1090 
1091  return cgltf_result_success;
1092 }

1094 static cgltf_size cgltf_calc_size(cgltf_type type, cgltf_component_type component_type);
1095 
1096 static cgltf_size cgltf_calc_index_bound(cgltf_buffer_view* buffer_view, cgltf_size offset, cgltf_component_type component_type, cgltf_size count)
1097 {
1098  char* data = (char*)buffer_view->buffer->data + offset + buffer_view->offset;
1099  cgltf_size bound = 0;
1100 
1101  switch (component_type)
1102  {
1103  case cgltf_component_type_r_8u:
1104  for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i)
1105  {
1106  cgltf_size v = ((unsigned char*)data)[i];
1107  bound = bound > v ? bound : v;
1108  }
1109  break;
1110 
1111  case cgltf_component_type_r_16u:
1112  for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i)
1113  {
1114  cgltf_size v = ((unsigned short*)data)[i];
1115  bound = bound > v ? bound : v;
1116  }
1117  break;
1118 
1119  case cgltf_component_type_r_32u:
1120  for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i)
1121  {
1122  cgltf_size v = ((unsigned int*)data)[i];
1123  bound = bound > v ? bound : v;
1124  }
1125  break;
1126 
1127  default:
1128  ;
1129  }
1130 
1131  return bound;
1132 }

1134 cgltf_result cgltf_validate(cgltf_data* data)
1135 {
1136  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->accessors_count; ++i)
1137  {
1138  cgltf_accessor* accessor = &data->accessors[i];
1139 
1140  cgltf_size element_size = cgltf_calc_size(accessor->type, accessor->component_type);
1141 
1142  if (accessor->buffer_view)
1143  {
1144  cgltf_size req_size = accessor->offset + accessor->stride * (accessor->count - 1) + element_size;
1145 
1146  if (accessor->buffer_view->size < req_size)
1147  {
1148  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
1149  }
1150  }
1151 
1152  if (accessor->is_sparse)
1153  {
1154  cgltf_accessor_sparse* sparse = &accessor->sparse;
1155 
1156  cgltf_size indices_component_size = cgltf_calc_size(cgltf_type_scalar, sparse->indices_component_type);
1157  cgltf_size indices_req_size = sparse->indices_byte_offset + indices_component_size * sparse->count;
1158  cgltf_size values_req_size = sparse->values_byte_offset + element_size * sparse->count;
1159 
1160  if (sparse->indices_buffer_view->size < indices_req_size ||
1161  sparse->values_buffer_view->size < values_req_size)
1162  {
1163  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
1164  }
1165 
1166  if (sparse->indices_component_type != cgltf_component_type_r_8u &&
1167  sparse->indices_component_type != cgltf_component_type_r_16u &&
1168  sparse->indices_component_type != cgltf_component_type_r_32u)
1169  {
1170  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1171  }
1172 
1173  if (sparse->indices_buffer_view->buffer->data)
1174  {
1175  cgltf_size index_bound = cgltf_calc_index_bound(sparse->indices_buffer_view, sparse->indices_byte_offset, sparse->indices_component_type, sparse->count);
1176 
1177  if (index_bound >= accessor->count)
1178  {
1179  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
1180  }
1181  }
1182  }
1183  }
1184 
1185  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->buffer_views_count; ++i)
1186  {
1187  cgltf_size req_size = data->buffer_views[i].offset + data->buffer_views[i].size;
1188 
1189  if (data->buffer_views[i].buffer && data->buffer_views[i].buffer->size < req_size)
1190  {
1191  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
1192  }
1193  }
1194 
1195  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->meshes_count; ++i)
1196  {
1197  if (data->meshes[i].weights)
1198  {
1199  if (data->meshes[i].primitives_count && data->meshes[i].primitives[0].targets_count != data->meshes[i].weights_count)
1200  {
1201  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1202  }
1203  }
1204 
1205  if (data->meshes[i].target_names)
1206  {
1207  if (data->meshes[i].primitives_count && data->meshes[i].primitives[0].targets_count != data->meshes[i].target_names_count)
1208  {
1209  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1210  }
1211  }
1212 
1213  for (cgltf_size j = 0; j < data->meshes[i].primitives_count; ++j)
1214  {
1215  if (data->meshes[i].primitives[j].targets_count != data->meshes[i].primitives[0].targets_count)
1216  {
1217  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1218  }
1219 
1220  if (data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes_count)
1221  {
1222  cgltf_accessor* first = data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes[0].data;
1223 
1224  for (cgltf_size k = 0; k < data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes_count; ++k)
1225  {
1226  if (data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes[k].data->count != first->count)
1227  {
1228  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1229  }
1230  }
1231 
1232  for (cgltf_size k = 0; k < data->meshes[i].primitives[j].targets_count; ++k)
1233  {
1234  for (cgltf_size m = 0; m < data->meshes[i].primitives[j].targets[k].attributes_count; ++m)
1235  {
1236  if (data->meshes[i].primitives[j].targets[k].attributes[m].data->count != first->count)
1237  {
1238  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1239  }
1240  }
1241  }
1242 
1243  cgltf_accessor* indices = data->meshes[i].primitives[j].indices;
1244 
1245  if (indices &&
1246  indices->component_type != cgltf_component_type_r_8u &&
1247  indices->component_type != cgltf_component_type_r_16u &&
1248  indices->component_type != cgltf_component_type_r_32u)
1249  {
1250  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1251  }
1252 
1253  if (indices && indices->buffer_view && indices->buffer_view->buffer->data)
1254  {
1255  cgltf_size index_bound = cgltf_calc_index_bound(indices->buffer_view, indices->offset, indices->component_type, indices->count);
1256 
1257  if (index_bound >= first->count)
1258  {
1259  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
1260  }
1261  }
1262  }
1263  }
1264  }
1265 
1266  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->nodes_count; ++i)
1267  {
1268  if (data->nodes[i].weights && data->nodes[i].mesh)
1269  {
1270  if (data->nodes[i].mesh->primitives_count && data->nodes[i].mesh->primitives[0].targets_count != data->nodes[i].weights_count)
1271  {
1272  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1273  }
1274  }
1275  }
1276 
1277  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->nodes_count; ++i)
1278  {
1279  cgltf_node* p1 = data->nodes[i].parent;
1280  cgltf_node* p2 = p1 ? p1->parent : NULL;
1281 
1282  while (p1 && p2)
1283  {
1284  if (p1 == p2)
1285  {
1286  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1287  }
1288 
1289  p1 = p1->parent;
1290  p2 = p2->parent ? p2->parent->parent : NULL;
1291  }
1292  }
1293 
1294  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->scenes_count; ++i)
1295  {
1296  for (cgltf_size j = 0; j < data->scenes[i].nodes_count; ++j)
1297  {
1298  if (data->scenes[i].nodes[j]->parent)
1299  {
1300  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1301  }
1302  }
1303  }
1304 
1305  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->animations_count; ++i)
1306  {
1307  for (cgltf_size j = 0; j < data->animations[i].channels_count; ++j)
1308  {
1309  cgltf_animation_channel* channel = &data->animations[i].channels[j];
1310 
1311  if (!channel->target_node)
1312  {
1313  continue;
1314  }
1315 
1316  cgltf_size components = 1;
1317 
1318  if (channel->target_path == cgltf_animation_path_type_weights)
1319  {
1320  if (!channel->target_node->mesh || !channel->target_node->mesh->primitives_count)
1321  {
1322  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
1323  }
1324 
1325  components = channel->target_node->mesh->primitives[0].targets_count;
1326  }
1327 
1328  cgltf_size values = channel->sampler->interpolation == cgltf_interpolation_type_cubic_spline ? 3 : 1;
1329 
1330  if (channel->sampler->input->count * components * values != channel->sampler->output->count)
1331  {
1332  return cgltf_result_data_too_short;
1333  }
1334  }
1335  }
1336 
1337  return cgltf_result_success;
1338 }

1357  dest[*dest_size - 1] = 0;
1358  }

1361  strncpy(dest, data->json + extras->start_offset, json_size);

1364 
1365  return cgltf_result_success;

1368 void cgltf_free(cgltf_data* data)
1369 {
1370  if (!data)
1371  {
1372  return;
1373  }
1374 
1375  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->asset.copyright);
1376  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->asset.generator);
1377  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->asset.version);
1378  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->asset.min_version);
1379 
1380  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->accessors);
1381  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->buffer_views);
1382 
1383  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->buffers_count; ++i)
1384  {
1385  if (data->buffers[i].data != data->bin)
1386  {
1387  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->buffers[i].data);
1388  }
1389 
1390  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->buffers[i].uri);
1391  }
1392 
1393  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->buffers);
1394 
1395  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->meshes_count; ++i)
1396  {
1397  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->meshes[i].name);
1398 
1399  for (cgltf_size j = 0; j < data->meshes[i].primitives_count; ++j)
1400  {
1401  for (cgltf_size k = 0; k < data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes_count; ++k)
1402  {
1403  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes[k].name);
1404  }
1405 
1406  data->memory_free(data->memory_user_data, data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes);
1407

1526 void cgltf_node_transform_local(const cgltf_node* node, cgltf_float* out_matrix)
1527 {
1528  cgltf_float* lm = out_matrix;
1529 
1530  if (node->has_matrix)
1531  {
1532  memcpy(lm, node->matrix, sizeof(float) * 16);
1533  }
1534  else
1535  {
1536  float tx = node->translation[0];
1537  float ty = node->translation[1];
1538  float tz = node->translation[2];
1539 
1540  float qx = node->rotation[0];
1541  float qy = node->rotation[1];
1542  float qz = node->rotation[2];
1543  float qw = node->rotation[3];
1544 
1545  float sx = node->scale[0];
1546  float sy = node->scale[1];
1547  float sz = node->scale[2];
1548 
1549  lm[0] = (1 - 2 * qy*qy - 2 * qz*qz) * sx;
1550  lm[1] = (2 * qx*qy + 2 * qz*qw) * sx;
1551  lm[2] = (2 * qx*qz - 2 * qy*qw) * sx;
1552  lm[3] = 0.f;
1553 
1554  lm[4] = (2 * qx*qy - 2 * qz*qw) * sy;
1555  lm[5] = (1 - 2 * qx*qx - 2 * qz*qz) * sy;
1556  lm[6] = (2 * qy*qz + 2 * qx*qw) * sy;
1557  lm[7] = 0.f;
1558 
1559  lm[8] = (2 * qx*qz + 2 * qy*qw) * sz;
1560  lm[9] = (2 * qy*qz - 2 * qx*qw) * sz;
1561  lm[10] = (1 - 2 * qx*qx - 2 * qy*qy) * sz;
1562  lm[11] = 0.f;
1563 
1564  lm[12] = tx;
1565  lm[13] = ty;
1566  lm[14] = tz;
1567  lm[15] = 1.f;
1568  }
1569 }

1571 void cgltf_node_transform_world(const cgltf_node* node, cgltf_float* out_matrix)
1572 {
1573  cgltf_float* lm = out_matrix;
1574  cgltf_node_transform_local(node, lm);
1575 
1576  const cgltf_node* parent = node->parent;
1577 
1578  while (parent)
1579  {
1580  float pm[16];
1581  cgltf_node_transform_local(parent, pm);
1582 
1583  for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
1584  {
1585  float l0 = lm[i * 4 + 0];
1586  float l1 = lm[i * 4 + 1];
1587  float l2 = lm[i * 4 + 2];
1588 
1589  float r0 = l0 * pm[0] + l1 * pm[4] + l2 * pm[8];
1590  float r1 = l0 * pm[1] + l1 * pm[5] + l2 * pm[9];
1591  float r2 = l0 * pm[2] + l1 * pm[6] + l2 * pm[10];
1592 
1593  lm[i * 4 + 0] = r0;
1594  lm[i * 4 + 1] = r1;
1595  lm[i * 4 + 2] = r2;
1596  }
1597 
1598  lm[12] += pm[12];
1599  lm[13] += pm[13];
1600  lm[14] += pm[14];
1601 
1602  parent = parent->parent;
1603  }
1604 }

1606 static cgltf_size cgltf_component_read_index(const void* in, cgltf_component_type component_type)
1607 {
1608  switch (component_type)
1609  {
1610  case cgltf_component_type_r_16:
1611  return *((const int16_t*) in);
1612  case cgltf_component_type_r_16u:
1613  return *((const uint16_t*) in);
1614  case cgltf_component_type_r_32u:
1615  return *((const uint32_t*) in);
1616  case cgltf_component_type_r_32f:
1617  return (cgltf_size)*((const float*) in);
1618  case cgltf_component_type_r_8:
1619  return *((const int8_t*) in);
1620  case cgltf_component_type_r_8u:
1621  return *((const uint8_t*) in);
1622  default:
1623  return 0;
1624  }
1625 }
1626 
1627 static cgltf_float cgltf_component_read_float(const void* in, cgltf_component_type component_type, cgltf_bool normalized)
1628 {
1629  if (component_type == cgltf_component_type_r_32f)
1630  {
1631  return *((const float*) in);
1632  }
1633 
1634  if (normalized)
1635  {
1636  switch (component_type)
1637  {
1638  // note: glTF spec doesn't currently define normalized conversions for 32-bit integers
1639  case cgltf_component_type_r_16:
1640  return *((const int16_t*) in) / (cgltf_float)32767;
1641  case cgltf_component_type_r_16u:
1642  return *((const uint16_t*) in) / (cgltf_float)65535;
1643  case cgltf_component_type_r_8:
1644  return *((const int8_t*) in) / (cgltf_float)127;
1645  case cgltf_component_type_r_8u:
1646  return *((const uint8_t*) in) / (cgltf_float)255;
1647  default:
1648  return 0;
1649  }
1650  }
1651 
1652  return (cgltf_float)cgltf_component_read_index(in, component_type);
1653 }
1654 
1655 static cgltf_size cgltf_component_size(cgltf_component_type component_type);
1656 
1657 static cgltf_bool cgltf_element_read_float(const uint8_t* element, cgltf_type type, cgltf_component_type component_type, cgltf_bool normalized, cgltf_float* out, cgltf_size element_size)
1658 {
1659  cgltf_size num_components = cgltf_num_components(type);
1660 
1661  if (element_size < num_components) {
1662  return 0;
1663  }
1664 
1665  // There are three special cases for component extraction, see #data-alignment in the 2.0 spec.
1666 
1667  cgltf_size component_size = cgltf_component_size(component_type);
1668 
1669  if (type == cgltf_type_mat2 && component_size == 1)
1670  {
1671  out[0] = cgltf_component_read_float(element, component_type, normalized);
1672  out[1] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 1, component_type, normalized);
1673  out[2] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 4, component_type, normalized);
1674  out[3] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 5, component_type, normalized);
1675  return 1;
1676  }
1677 
1678  if (type == cgltf_type_mat3 && component_size == 1)
1679  {
1680  out[0] = cgltf_component_read_float(element, component_type, normalized);
1681  out[1] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 1, component_type, normalized);
1682  out[2] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 2, component_type, normalized);
1683  out[3] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 4, component_type, normalized);
1684  out[4] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 5, component_type, normalized);
1685  out[5] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 6, component_type, normalized);
1686  out[6] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 8, component_type, normalized);
1687  out[7] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 9, component_type, normalized);
1688  out[8] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 10, component_type, normalized);
1689  return 1;
1690  }
1691 
1692  if (type == cgltf_type_mat3 && component_size == 2)
1693  {
1694  out[0] = cgltf_component_read_float(element, component_type, normalized);
1695  out[1] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 2, component_type, normalized);
1696  out[2] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 4, component_type, normalized);
1697  out[3] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 8, component_type, normalized);
1698  out[4] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 10, component_type, normalized);
1699  out[5] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 12, component_type, normalized);
1700  out[6] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 16, component_type, normalized);
1701  out[7] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 18, component_type, normalized);
1702  out[8] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + 20, component_type, normalized);
1703  return 1;
1704  }
1705 
1706  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < num_components; ++i)
1707  {
1708  out[i] = cgltf_component_read_float(element + component_size * i, component_type, normalized);
1709  }
1710  return 1;
1711 }

1713 cgltf_bool cgltf_accessor_read_float(const cgltf_accessor* accessor, cgltf_size index, cgltf_float* out, cgltf_size element_size)
1714 {
1715  if (accessor->is_sparse)
1716  {
1717  return 0;
1718  }
1719  if (accessor->buffer_view == NULL)
1720  {
1721  memset(out, 0, element_size * sizeof(cgltf_float));
1722  return 1;
1723  }
1724  if (accessor->buffer_view->buffer->data == NULL)
1725  {
1726  return 0;
1727  }
1728  cgltf_size offset = accessor->offset + accessor->buffer_view->offset;
1729  const uint8_t* element = (const uint8_t*) accessor->buffer_view->buffer->data;
1730  element += offset + accessor->stride * index;
1731  return cgltf_element_read_float(element, accessor->type, accessor->component_type, accessor->normalized, out, element_size);
1732 }
1733 
1734 cgltf_size cgltf_accessor_unpack_floats(const cgltf_accessor* accessor, cgltf_float* out, cgltf_size float_count)
1735 {
1736  cgltf_size floats_per_element = cgltf_num_components(accessor->type);
1737  cgltf_size available_floats = accessor->count * floats_per_element;
1738  if (out == NULL)
1739  {
1740  return available_floats;
1741  }
1742 
1743  float_count = available_floats < float_count ? available_floats : float_count;
1744  cgltf_size element_count = float_count / floats_per_element;
1745 
1746  // First pass: convert each element in the base accessor.
1747  cgltf_float* dest = out;
1748  cgltf_accessor dense = *accessor;
1749  dense.is_sparse = 0;
1750  for (cgltf_size index = 0; index < element_count; index++, dest += floats_per_element)
1751  {
1752  if (!cgltf_accessor_read_float(&dense, index, dest, floats_per_element))
1753  {
1754  return 0;
1755  }
1756  }
1757 
1758  // Second pass: write out each element in the sparse accessor.
1759  if (accessor->is_sparse)
1760  {
1761  const cgltf_accessor_sparse* sparse = &dense.sparse;
1762 
1763  if (sparse->indices_buffer_view->buffer->data == NULL || sparse->values_buffer_view->buffer->data == NULL)
1764  {
1765  return 0;
1766  }
1767 
1768  const uint8_t* index_data = (const uint8_t*) sparse->indices_buffer_view->buffer->data;
1769  index_data += sparse->indices_byte_offset + sparse->indices_buffer_view->offset;
1770  cgltf_size index_stride = cgltf_component_size(sparse->indices_component_type);
1771  const uint8_t* reader_head = (const uint8_t*) sparse->values_buffer_view->buffer->data;
1772  reader_head += sparse->values_byte_offset + sparse->values_buffer_view->offset;
1773  for (cgltf_size reader_index = 0; reader_index < sparse->count; reader_index++, index_data += index_stride)
1774  {
1775  size_t writer_index = cgltf_component_read_index(index_data, sparse->indices_component_type);
1776  float* writer_head = out + writer_index * floats_per_element;
1777 
1778  if (!cgltf_element_read_float(reader_head, dense.type, dense.component_type, dense.normalized, writer_head, floats_per_element))
1779  {
1780  return 0;
1781  }
1782 
1783  reader_head += dense.stride;
1784  }
1785  }
1786 
1787  return element_count * floats_per_element;
1788 }

1791 {
1792  if (accessor->is_sparse)

1794  return 0; // This is an error case, but we can't communicate the error with existing interface.

1856 static int cgltf_skip_json(jsmntok_t const* tokens, int i)
1857 {

1859 
1860  while (i < end)
1861  {

1864  case JSMN_OBJECT:

1866  break;
1867

1871 
1872  case JSMN_PRIMITIVE:
1873  case JSMN_STRING:

1911 static int cgltf_parse_json_string(cgltf_options* options, jsmntok_t const* tokens, int i, const uint8_t* json_chunk, char** out_string)
1912 {
1913  CGLTF_CHECK_TOKTYPE(tokens[i], JSMN_STRING);
1914  if (*out_string)
1915  {
1916  return CGLTF_ERROR_JSON;
1917  }
1918  int size = tokens[i].end - tokens[i].start;
1919  char* result = (char*)options->memory_alloc(options->memory_user_data, size + 1);
1920  if (!result)
1921  {
1922  return CGLTF_ERROR_NOMEM;
1923  }
1924  strncpy(result, (const char*)json_chunk + tokens[i].start, size);
1925  result[size] = 0;
1926  *out_string = result;
1927  return i + 1;

1972 static void cgltf_parse_attribute_type(const char* name, cgltf_attribute_type* out_type, int* out_index)
1973 {
1974  const char* us = strchr(name, '_');
1975  size_t len = us ? (size_t)(us - name) : strlen(name);
1976 
1977  if (len == 8 && strncmp(name, "POSITION", 8) == 0)
1978  {
1979  *out_type = cgltf_attribute_type_position;
1980  }
1981  else if (len == 6 && strncmp(name, "NORMAL", 6) == 0)
1982  {
1983  *out_type = cgltf_attribute_type_normal;
1984  }
1985  else if (len == 7 && strncmp(name, "TANGENT", 7) == 0)
1986  {
1987  *out_type = cgltf_attribute_type_tangent;
1988  }
1989  else if (len == 8 && strncmp(name, "TEXCOORD", 8) == 0)
1990  {
1991  *out_type = cgltf_attribute_type_texcoord;
1992  }
1993  else if (len == 5 && strncmp(name, "COLOR", 5) == 0)
1994  {
1995  *out_type = cgltf_attribute_type_color;
1996  }
1997  else if (len == 6 && strncmp(name, "JOINTS", 6) == 0)
1998  {
1999  *out_type = cgltf_attribute_type_joints;
2000  }
2001  else if (len == 7 && strncmp(name, "WEIGHTS", 7) == 0)
2002  {
2003  *out_type = cgltf_attribute_type_weights;
2004  }
2005  else
2006  {
2007  *out_type = cgltf_attribute_type_invalid;
2008  }
2009 
2010  if (us && *out_type != cgltf_attribute_type_invalid)
2011  {
2012  *out_index = CGLTF_ATOI(us + 1);
2013  }
2014 }

4167 cgltf_size cgltf_num_components(cgltf_type type) {
4168  switch (type)
4169  {
4170  case cgltf_type_vec2:
4171  return 2;
4172  case cgltf_type_vec3:
4173  return 3;
4174  case cgltf_type_vec4:
4175  return 4;
4176  case cgltf_type_mat2:
4177  return 4;
4178  case cgltf_type_mat3:
4179  return 9;
4180  case cgltf_type_mat4:
4181  return 16;
4182  case cgltf_type_invalid:
4183  case cgltf_type_scalar:
4184  default:
4185  return 1;

4187 }

4189 static cgltf_size cgltf_component_size(cgltf_component_type component_type) {
4190  switch (component_type)
4191  {
4192  case cgltf_component_type_r_8:
4193  case cgltf_component_type_r_8u:
4194  return 1;
4195  case cgltf_component_type_r_16:
4196  case cgltf_component_type_r_16u:
4197  return 2;
4198  case cgltf_component_type_r_32u:
4199  case cgltf_component_type_r_32f:
4200  return 4;

4202  default:
4203  return 0;
4204  }

4207 static cgltf_size cgltf_calc_size(cgltf_type type, cgltf_component_type component_type)
4208 {
4209  cgltf_size component_size = cgltf_component_size(component_type);
4210  if (type == cgltf_type_mat2 && component_size == 1)
4211  {
4212  return 8 * component_size;
4213  }
4214  else if (type == cgltf_type_mat3 && (component_size == 1 || component_size == 2))
4215  {
4216  return 12 * component_size;
4217  }
4218  return component_size * cgltf_num_components(type);
4219 }

4374 cgltf_result cgltf_parse_json(cgltf_options* options, const uint8_t* json_chunk, cgltf_size size, cgltf_data** out_data)
4375 {
4376  jsmn_parser parser = { 0, 0, 0 };
4377 
4378  if (options->json_token_count == 0)
4379  {
4380  int token_count = jsmn_parse(&parser, (const char*)json_chunk, size, NULL, 0);
4381 
4382  if (token_count <= 0)
4383  {
4384  return cgltf_result_invalid_json;
4385  }
4386 
4387  options->json_token_count = token_count;
4388  }
4389 
4390  jsmntok_t* tokens = (jsmntok_t*)options->memory_alloc(options->memory_user_data, sizeof(jsmntok_t) * (options->json_token_count + 1));
4391 
4392  if (!tokens)
4393  {
4394  return cgltf_result_out_of_memory;
4395  }
4396 
4397  jsmn_init(&parser);
4398 
4399  int token_count = jsmn_parse(&parser, (const char*)json_chunk, size, tokens, options->json_token_count);
4400 
4401  if (token_count <= 0)
4402  {
4403  options->memory_free(options->memory_user_data, tokens);
4404  return cgltf_result_invalid_json;
4405  }
4406 
4407  // this makes sure that we always have an UNDEFINED token at the end of the stream
4408  // for invalid JSON inputs this makes sure we don't perform out of bound reads of token data
4409  tokens[token_count].type = JSMN_UNDEFINED;
4410 
4411  cgltf_data* data = (cgltf_data*)options->memory_alloc(options->memory_user_data, sizeof(cgltf_data));
4412 
4413  if (!data)
4414  {
4415  options->memory_free(options->memory_user_data, tokens);
4416  return cgltf_result_out_of_memory;
4417  }
4418 
4419  memset(data, 0, sizeof(cgltf_data));
4420  data->memory_free = options->memory_free;
4421  data->memory_user_data = options->memory_user_data;
4422 
4423  int i = cgltf_parse_json_root(options, tokens, 0, json_chunk, data);
4424 
4425  options->memory_free(options->memory_user_data, tokens);
4426 
4427  if (i < 0)
4428  {
4429  cgltf_free(data);
4430 
4431  switch (i)
4432  {
4433  case CGLTF_ERROR_NOMEM: return cgltf_result_out_of_memory;
4434  case CGLTF_ERROR_LEGACY: return cgltf_result_legacy_gltf;
4435  default: return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
4436  }
4437  }
4438 
4439  if (cgltf_fixup_pointers(data) < 0)
4440  {
4441  cgltf_free(data);
4442  return cgltf_result_invalid_gltf;
4443  }
4444 
4445  data->json = (const char*)json_chunk;
4446  data->json_size = size;
4447 
4448  *out_data = data;
4449 
4450  return cgltf_result_success;
4451 }

4453 static int cgltf_fixup_pointers(cgltf_data* data)
4454 {
4455  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->meshes_count; ++i)
4456  {
4457  for (cgltf_size j = 0; j < data->meshes[i].primitives_count; ++j)
4458  {
4459  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->meshes[i].primitives[j].indices, data->accessors, data->accessors_count);
4460  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->meshes[i].primitives[j].material, data->materials, data->materials_count);
4461 
4462  for (cgltf_size k = 0; k < data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes_count; ++k)
4463  {
4464  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->meshes[i].primitives[j].attributes[k].data, data->accessors, data->accessors_count);
4465  }
4466 
4467  for (cgltf_size k = 0; k < data->meshes[i].primitives[j].targets_count; ++k)
4468  {
4469  for (cgltf_size m = 0; m < data->meshes[i].primitives[j].targets[k].attributes_count; ++m)
4470  {
4471  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->meshes[i].primitives[j].targets[k].attributes[m].data, data->accessors, data->accessors_count);
4472  }
4473  }
4474  }
4475  }
4476 
4477  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->accessors_count; ++i)
4478  {
4479  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->accessors[i].buffer_view, data->buffer_views, data->buffer_views_count);
4480 
4481  if (data->accessors[i].is_sparse)
4482  {
4483  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->accessors[i].sparse.indices_buffer_view, data->buffer_views, data->buffer_views_count);
4484  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->accessors[i].sparse.values_buffer_view, data->buffer_views, data->buffer_views_count);
4485  }
4486 
4487  if (data->accessors[i].buffer_view)
4488  {
4489  data->accessors[i].stride = data->accessors[i].buffer_view->stride;
4490  }
4491 
4492  if (data->accessors[i].stride == 0)
4493  {
4494  data->accessors[i].stride = cgltf_calc_size(data->accessors[i].type, data->accessors[i].component_type);
4495  }
4496  }
4497 
4498  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->textures_count; ++i)
4499  {
4500  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->textures[i].image, data->images, data->images_count);
4501  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->textures[i].sampler, data->samplers, data->samplers_count);
4502  }
4503 
4504  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->images_count; ++i)
4505  {
4506  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->images[i].buffer_view, data->buffer_views, data->buffer_views_count);
4507  }
4508 
4509  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->materials_count; ++i)
4510  {
4511  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->materials[i].normal_texture.texture, data->textures, data->textures_count);
4512  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->materials[i].emissive_texture.texture, data->textures, data->textures_count);
4513  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->materials[i].occlusion_texture.texture, data->textures, data->textures_count);
4514 
4515  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->materials[i].pbr_metallic_roughness.base_color_texture.texture, data->textures, data->textures_count);
4516  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->materials[i].pbr_metallic_roughness.metallic_roughness_texture.texture, data->textures, data->textures_count);
4517 
4518  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->materials[i].pbr_specular_glossiness.diffuse_texture.texture, data->textures, data->textures_count);
4519  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->materials[i].pbr_specular_glossiness.specular_glossiness_texture.texture, data->textures, data->textures_count);
4520  }
4521 
4522  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->buffer_views_count; ++i)

4524  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->buffer_views[i].buffer, data->buffers, data->buffers_count);
4525  }
4526 
4527  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->skins_count; ++i)
4528  {

4530  {
4531  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->skins[i].joints[j], data->nodes, data->nodes_count);
4532  }
4533 
4534  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->skins[i].skeleton, data->nodes, data->nodes_count);
4535  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->skins[i].inverse_bind_matrices, data->accessors, data->accessors_count);
4536  }
4537 
4538  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->nodes_count; ++i)
4539  {
4540  for (cgltf_size j = 0; j < data->nodes[i].children_count; ++j)
4541  {
4542  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->nodes[i].children[j], data->nodes, data->nodes_count);
4543 
4544  if (data->nodes[i].children[j]->parent)
4545  {

4563 
4564  if (data->scenes[i].nodes[j]->parent)

4566  return CGLTF_ERROR_JSON;

4569  }
4570 
4571  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->scene, data->scenes, data->scenes_count);
4572 
4573  for (cgltf_size i = 0; i < data->animations_count; ++i)
4574  {
4575  for (cgltf_size j = 0; j < data->animations[i].samplers_count; ++j)
4576  {
4577  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->animations[i].samplers[j].input, data->accessors, data->accessors_count);
4578  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->animations[i].samplers[j].output, data->accessors, data->accessors_count);
4579  }

4581  for (cgltf_size j = 0; j < data->animations[i].channels_count; ++j)

4583  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP_REQ(data->animations[i].channels[j].sampler, data->animations[i].samplers, data->animations[i].samplers_count);
4584  CGLTF_PTRFIXUP(data->animations[i].channels[j].target_node, data->nodes, data->nodes_count);
4585  }
4586  }
4587 
4588  return 0;

4620 static jsmntok_t *jsmn_alloc_token(jsmn_parser *parser,
4621  jsmntok_t *tokens, size_t num_tokens) {
4622  jsmntok_t *tok;
4623  if (parser->toknext >= num_tokens) {
4624  return NULL;
4625  }
4626  tok = &tokens[parser->toknext++];
4627  tok->start = tok->end = -1;
4628  tok->size = 0;
4629 #ifdef JSMN_PARENT_LINKS
4630  tok->parent = -1;
4631 #endif
4632  return tok;
4633 }

4638 static void jsmn_fill_token(jsmntok_t *token, jsmntype_t type,
4639  int start, int end) {
4640  token->type = type;
4641  token->start = start;
4642  token->end = end;
4643  token->size = 0;
4644 }

4649 static int jsmn_parse_primitive(jsmn_parser *parser, const char *js,
4650  size_t len, jsmntok_t *tokens, size_t num_tokens) {
4651  jsmntok_t *token;
4652  int start;
4653 
4654  start = parser->pos;
4655 
4656  for (; parser->pos < len && js[parser->pos] != '\0'; parser->pos++) {
4657  switch (js[parser->pos]) {
4658 #ifndef JSMN_STRICT
4659  /* In strict mode primitive must be followed by "," or "}" or "]" */
4660  case ':':
4661 #endif
4662  case '\t' : case '\r' : case '\n' : case ' ' :
4663  case ',' : case ']' : case '}' :
4664  goto found;
4665  }
4666  if (js[parser->pos] < 32 || js[parser->pos] >= 127) {
4667  parser->pos = start;
4668  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4669  }
4670  }
4671 #ifdef JSMN_STRICT
4672  /* In strict mode primitive must be followed by a comma/object/array */
4673  parser->pos = start;
4674  return JSMN_ERROR_PART;
4675 #endif
4676 
4677 found:
4678  if (tokens == NULL) {
4679  parser->pos--;
4680  return 0;
4681  }
4682  token = jsmn_alloc_token(parser, tokens, num_tokens);
4683  if (token == NULL) {
4684  parser->pos = start;
4685  return JSMN_ERROR_NOMEM;
4686  }
4687  jsmn_fill_token(token, JSMN_PRIMITIVE, start, parser->pos);
4688 #ifdef JSMN_PARENT_LINKS
4689  token->parent = parser->toksuper;
4690 #endif
4691  parser->pos--;
4692  return 0;
4693 }
4694 
4698 static int jsmn_parse_string(jsmn_parser *parser, const char *js,
4699  size_t len, jsmntok_t *tokens, size_t num_tokens) {
4700  jsmntok_t *token;
4701 
4702  int start = parser->pos;
4703 
4704  parser->pos++;
4705 
4706  /* Skip starting quote */
4707  for (; parser->pos < len && js[parser->pos] != '\0'; parser->pos++) {
4708  char c = js[parser->pos];
4709 
4710  /* Quote: end of string */
4711  if (c == '\"') {
4712  if (tokens == NULL) {
4713  return 0;
4714  }
4715  token = jsmn_alloc_token(parser, tokens, num_tokens);
4716  if (token == NULL) {
4717  parser->pos = start;
4718  return JSMN_ERROR_NOMEM;
4719  }
4720  jsmn_fill_token(token, JSMN_STRING, start+1, parser->pos);
4721 #ifdef JSMN_PARENT_LINKS
4722  token->parent = parser->toksuper;
4723 #endif
4724  return 0;
4725  }
4726 
4727  /* Backslash: Quoted symbol expected */
4728  if (c == '\\' && parser->pos + 1 < len) {
4729  int i;
4730  parser->pos++;
4731  switch (js[parser->pos]) {
4732  /* Allowed escaped symbols */
4733  case '\"': case '/' : case '\\' : case 'b' :
4734  case 'f' : case 'r' : case 'n' : case 't' :
4735  break;
4736  /* Allows escaped symbol \uXXXX */
4737  case 'u':
4738  parser->pos++;
4739  for(i = 0; i < 4 && parser->pos < len && js[parser->pos] != '\0'; i++) {
4740  /* If it isn't a hex character we have an error */
4741  if(!((js[parser->pos] >= 48 && js[parser->pos] <= 57) || /* 0-9 */
4742  (js[parser->pos] >= 65 && js[parser->pos] <= 70) || /* A-F */
4743  (js[parser->pos] >= 97 && js[parser->pos] <= 102))) { /* a-f */
4744  parser->pos = start;
4745  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4746  }
4747  parser->pos++;
4748  }
4749  parser->pos--;
4750  break;
4751  /* Unexpected symbol */
4752  default:
4753  parser->pos = start;
4754  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4755  }
4756  }
4757  }
4758  parser->pos = start;
4759  return JSMN_ERROR_PART;
4760 }
4761 
4765 static int jsmn_parse(jsmn_parser *parser, const char *js, size_t len,
4766  jsmntok_t *tokens, size_t num_tokens) {
4767  int r;
4768  int i;
4769  jsmntok_t *token;
4770  int count = parser->toknext;
4771 
4772  for (; parser->pos < len && js[parser->pos] != '\0'; parser->pos++) {
4773  char c;
4774  jsmntype_t type;
4775 
4776  c = js[parser->pos];
4777  switch (c) {
4778  case '{': case '[':
4779  count++;
4780  if (tokens == NULL) {
4781  break;
4782  }
4783  token = jsmn_alloc_token(parser, tokens, num_tokens);
4784  if (token == NULL)
4785  return JSMN_ERROR_NOMEM;
4786  if (parser->toksuper != -1) {
4787  tokens[parser->toksuper].size++;
4788 #ifdef JSMN_PARENT_LINKS
4789  token->parent = parser->toksuper;
4790 #endif
4791  }
4792  token->type = (c == '{' ? JSMN_OBJECT : JSMN_ARRAY);
4793  token->start = parser->pos;
4794  parser->toksuper = parser->toknext - 1;
4795  break;
4796  case '}': case ']':
4797  if (tokens == NULL)
4798  break;
4799  type = (c == '}' ? JSMN_OBJECT : JSMN_ARRAY);
4800 #ifdef JSMN_PARENT_LINKS
4801  if (parser->toknext < 1) {
4802  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4803  }
4804  token = &tokens[parser->toknext - 1];
4805  for (;;) {
4806  if (token->start != -1 && token->end == -1) {
4807  if (token->type != type) {
4808  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4809  }
4810  token->end = parser->pos + 1;
4811  parser->toksuper = token->parent;
4812  break;
4813  }
4814  if (token->parent == -1) {
4815  if(token->type != type || parser->toksuper == -1) {
4816  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4817  }
4818  break;
4819  }
4820  token = &tokens[token->parent];
4821  }
4822 #else
4823  for (i = parser->toknext - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4824  token = &tokens[i];
4825  if (token->start != -1 && token->end == -1) {
4826  if (token->type != type) {
4827  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4828  }
4829  parser->toksuper = -1;
4830  token->end = parser->pos + 1;
4831  break;
4832  }
4833  }
4834  /* Error if unmatched closing bracket */
4835  if (i == -1) return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4836  for (; i >= 0; i--) {
4837  token = &tokens[i];
4838  if (token->start != -1 && token->end == -1) {
4839  parser->toksuper = i;
4840  break;
4841  }
4842  }
4843 #endif
4844  break;
4845  case '\"':
4846  r = jsmn_parse_string(parser, js, len, tokens, num_tokens);
4847  if (r < 0) return r;
4848  count++;
4849  if (parser->toksuper != -1 && tokens != NULL)
4850  tokens[parser->toksuper].size++;
4851  break;
4852  case '\t' : case '\r' : case '\n' : case ' ':
4853  break;
4854  case ':':
4855  parser->toksuper = parser->toknext - 1;
4856  break;
4857  case ',':
4858  if (tokens != NULL && parser->toksuper != -1 &&
4859  tokens[parser->toksuper].type != JSMN_ARRAY &&
4860  tokens[parser->toksuper].type != JSMN_OBJECT) {
4861 #ifdef JSMN_PARENT_LINKS
4862  parser->toksuper = tokens[parser->toksuper].parent;
4863 #else
4864  for (i = parser->toknext - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4865  if (tokens[i].type == JSMN_ARRAY || tokens[i].type == JSMN_OBJECT) {
4866  if (tokens[i].start != -1 && tokens[i].end == -1) {
4867  parser->toksuper = i;
4868  break;
4869  }
4870  }
4871  }
4872 #endif
4873  }
4874  break;
4875 #ifdef JSMN_STRICT
4876  /* In strict mode primitives are: numbers and booleans */
4877  case '-': case '0': case '1' : case '2': case '3' : case '4':
4878  case '5': case '6': case '7' : case '8': case '9':
4879  case 't': case 'f': case 'n' :
4880  /* And they must not be keys of the object */
4881  if (tokens != NULL && parser->toksuper != -1) {
4882  jsmntok_t *t = &tokens[parser->toksuper];
4883  if (t->type == JSMN_OBJECT ||
4884  (t->type == JSMN_STRING && t->size != 0)) {
4885  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4886  }
4887  }
4888 #else
4889  /* In non-strict mode every unquoted value is a primitive */
4890  default:
4891 #endif
4892  r = jsmn_parse_primitive(parser, js, len, tokens, num_tokens);
4893  if (r < 0) return r;
4894  count++;
4895  if (parser->toksuper != -1 && tokens != NULL)
4896  tokens[parser->toksuper].size++;
4897  break;
4898 
4899 #ifdef JSMN_STRICT
4900  /* Unexpected char in strict mode */
4901  default:
4902  return JSMN_ERROR_INVAL;
4903 #endif
4904  }
4905  }
4906 
4907  if (tokens != NULL) {
4908  for (i = parser->toknext - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4909  /* Unmatched opened object or array */
4910  if (tokens[i].start != -1 && tokens[i].end == -1) {
4911  return JSMN_ERROR_PART;
4912  }
4913  }
4914  }
4915 
4916  return count;
4917 }
4918 
4923 static void jsmn_init(jsmn_parser *parser) {
4924  parser->pos = 0;
4925  parser->toknext = 0;
4926  parser->toksuper = -1;
4927 }
4928 /*
4929  * -- jsmn.c end --
4930  */
